# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the Python is
#   managed by the developer. For a project/app, you might want to check these files in.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1191, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in cases where the lockfile contains platform-specific dependencies, it may cause issues.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, see https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-lock-file-to-version-control
